Holy Redemption failed as a guild because we didnt have anyone to lead raids, not enough showed up on time, etc.<br>
<br>
Most people get to a point where they are 50+  or 54+,<br>
and NEED to do things appropriate for their level.<br>
<br>
Yes my other post was a joke about me leaving.<br>
BUT  (this is not a threat) if we are not successful with raiding,  At some point I will leave KoV for a guild that is.<br>
Friends in Omani and HoN have been after me for a while to join them.   <br>
But no, I am not leaving anytime soon,  and in at least<br>
ONE scenario, I can see KoV being as successful, As I would need a guild to be.   This MAY be my final EQ Home.<br>
<br>
BUT  raiding is a skill,<br>
It requires<br>
Punctuality,<br>
Ablity to LISTEN,<br>
Ablity to FOLLOW Orders,<br>
A strong leader,<br>
dedication,<br>
and Teamwork.<br>
(probably a few other things as well.)<br>
<br>
IF KoV is to thrive as a guild  (family guild or otherwise)<br>
We will have to be successful at Raiding.<br>
We will have to go some of the tougher places.<br>
WE are almost all 50+ now and we need to act like it.<br>
I know I haven't, but hopefully now we can ALL take that step together.<br>
