<br>
Are we going to get our butts in gear as a group,<br>
and be successful at raiding.<br>
<br>
It's only a matter of putting our minds to it.<br>
<br>
We did DN the other day after cancelling Kael (it was camped)<br>
I know I hadn't read up on the zone, but I didn't think we were going there.<br>
I hadn't read up on SG either for that matter,<br>
Nor CS, Nor WW.<br>
<br>
One thing I want to point out for the MA's  and SA's and chanters etc.<br>
(and no I don't want anyone to get offeded just a friendly tip)<br>
<br>
make sure you call for MEZ or for ATTACK is clear.<br>
<br>
IMHO a sample ideal  call for attack.<br>
<br>
/shout =EVERYONE ATTACK NOW= ATTACKING <<<<<< %t >>>>>>><br>
<br>
the arrow brackets  add to the length of the message,<br>
and make it clear what the mob is.<br>
My ooc was spamming right along. my ooc and shout are fairly close in color.<br>
<br>
Incoming calls<br>
Attack calls<br>
Mez Calls  <br>
should be a hot key,<br>
should be one line only<br>
should be the full legnth of the line allowed<br>
should be hit more than once   <br>
no sense having someone miss it <br>
should be hit after the MA gets a taunt or two off.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
PEELING<br>
If we are using an FD puller<br>
the MA should be 10 yards in front of everyone else<br>
the puller should FD at the feet of the MA when the mob arrives<br>
the MA should taunt and attack and then after a few hits and a couple taunts should hit the call for attack hot key<br>
and then keep taunting.<br>
<br>
Erveryone(melee) should rush up to the MA and attack<br>
but when the mob is dead<br>
everyone (melee) should go back up again 10 yards behind MA<br>
to repeat.<br>
<br>
I don't know why im writing this hear,  IMHO the people who need to read this don't read the boards.<br>
