                Here's another rant that I have too! *Jens on a roll*  I really don't think ANYONE should be speaking in /OOC or /Shout unless they are running the raid. This creates unwarranted spam and important instructions are missed and people die. Oh! And the E-motes! Sometimes I just wanna puke! This one kissing this one, hugging, dancing, pointing.....BLEH!BLEH! BLEH! BLEH!YUKKERS! I know - I know...everyone wants to have fun and is excited to see eachother....Let's get the raid going..<br>
                Yes, I can be mushy too but during the raid it's annoying. More spam I gotta look through to get my instructions.....sure, you can turn the e-motes off................but still. Raids are pretty serious to me. I want to attain the goal of the raid....whether it's to get an epic or just loot. I want to get there and get the job done! There is NO reason it should take more than an hour to get a raid going.<br>
